5 core functions of NIST Framework
Identify - what assets (data, hardware, software, etc.) do we have? 
Protect - how do we prevent damage to the assets?  
Detect - how do we know we’re under attack? 
Respond - what do we do immediately in case of an attack?
Recover - how do we restore operations?

CIA Triad
Confidentiality: prevent unauthorized access to data
Cloud example: encrypting S3 buckets

Integrity: data can’t be altered without authorization
Cloud example: hash verification

Availability: systems must remain accessible when needed
Cloud example: redundant servers
